      "fontSize": 44.96475621228546,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "Programming means getting a program \nworking. You have a problem to solve, you \nwrite some Go code, you run it, you get your\nanswer, you’re done. That’s programming, and\nthat’s difficult enough by itself.",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Programming means getting a program working. You have a problem to solve, you write some Go code, you run it, you get your answer, you’re done. That’s programming, and that’s difficult enough by itself.",
